headline: 2 Reasons to Like BR and 1 to Stay Skeptical
summary: Even during a down period for the markets, Broadridge has gone against the grain, climbing to $235. Its shares have yielded a 8.4% return over the last six months, beating the S&P 500 by 16.5%. This was partly thanks to its solid quarterly results, and the run-up might have investors contemplating their next move.
